---
import TradeHubLayout from '../layouts/TradeHubLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Building work is complex — how does the AI handle detailed enquiries?",
    answer: "The AI doesn't try to understand the technical details of your building work — that's your expertise. What it does is capture the customer's requirements in their own words: 'We want a single-storey rear extension,' 'We need a loft conversion with a dormer,' 'The chimney breast needs removing,' or 'We want to convert the garage into a bedroom.' It records the property type, the scope as described by the customer, their timeline, and their contact details. You then follow up with the detailed conversation about specifications, planning, and pricing."
  },
  {
    question: "I run a small building firm with a team — can the AI handle calls for the whole business?",
    answer: "Yes. The AI answers with your company name and handles calls as your business receptionist. Whether you're a sole trader or you've got a team of ten, the AI captures every enquiry — from new project leads to existing customers checking on progress. It doesn't matter if you're all on site simultaneously; every call is answered and every lead is recorded."
  },
  {
    question: "A lot of my work comes from architects, surveyors, and other professionals. Can the AI handle those calls?",
    answer: "Professional referral calls are often your best leads — they come pre-qualified and the customer usually has budget approval. When an architect calls to discuss a project, a surveyor recommends a structural repair, or a planning consultant sends a client your way, the AI captures the referral source, the project details, and the timeline. These are relationship leads, and the AI makes a professional first impression that reflects well on both you and the referring professional."
  },
  {
    question: "Building projects run for weeks or months. Do existing customers call back through the AI?",
    answer: "Yes, and it's useful for managing ongoing communication. If a customer calls to check when your team is arriving, report an issue with work completed, or discuss a variation, the AI captures their message and sends it to you. This means you're never blindsided by a customer complaint you didn't know about, and your clients always feel heard — even when you're neck-deep in a foundation dig."
  },
  {
    question: "Does the AI understand planning permission and Building Regs?",
    answer: "The AI never discusses planning permission requirements, Building Regulations, structural calculations, or party wall agreements with callers. Those are complex, project-specific conversations that need your professional judgement. The AI captures what the customer wants to do and their concerns, then sends everything to you. The regulatory conversation happens during your site visit or consultation."
  },
  {
    question: "I do everything from small repairs to full house builds. Can the AI handle that range?",
    answer: "The beauty of building work is its variety, and the AI handles enquiries across the full spectrum. A homeowner who needs a cracked lintel replacing gets the same professional response as a developer who wants a quote for a commercial fit-out. A elderly customer needing a grab rail installed is treated with the same care as a project manager running a multi-phase renovation. Every enquiry is captured with appropriate detail, regardless of scale."
  },
  {
    question: "What about emergency structural work — collapsed walls, dangerous structures?",
    answer: "Structural emergencies are treated with the highest priority. If a caller describes a collapsing wall, a dangerous structure, subsidence damage, or storm damage to a building, the AI escalates immediately. It captures whether anyone is at risk, whether the property is occupied, and the nature of the structural concern. These calls reach you within seconds, because structural emergencies can't wait for a callback."
  },
  {
    question: "How does this compare to relying on word-of-mouth?",
    answer: "Word-of-mouth is the lifeblood of any building business — and it still requires someone to answer when the referral calls. A recommendation from a happy customer is worthless if the referred customer gets your voicemail and calls a competitor instead. Rapid Receptionist makes sure every recommendation call is answered instantly, the customer feels valued, and you get the lead details to follow up. It doesn't replace word-of-mouth — it makes sure word-of-mouth actually converts."
  }
];
---

<TradeHubLayout
  title="AI Receptionist for UK Builders — Never Miss a Job | Rapid Receptionist"
  description="AI receptionist built for UK builders. Handles extension enquiries, renovation leads & emergency structural calls 24/7. Only £99/mo."
  canonicalUrl="/ai-receptionist-for-builders/"
  tradeName="Builder"
  tradeNamePlural="Builders"
  tradeSlug="builders"
  headline="The AI Receptionist Built for UK Builders. Every Lead Laid Down."
  accentWord="UK Builders"
  subhead="You're on site from dawn, covered in dust, and your phone's ringing somewhere in your tool bag. Extensions, loft conversions, renovations — the leads keep coming, but you can't answer when you're pouring concrete or setting steels."
  speedStat="The average UK builder loses £24,000 a year from missed calls."
  speedText="That figure isn't hypothetical — it's the calculated revenue lost when 62% of calls go unanswered. For builders, where individual jobs run into thousands or tens of thousands, even one missed call per week adds up catastrophically over a year."
  scenario="It's 8am on a Tuesday. You're on a loft conversion in Watford — your joiner is fitting the dormer frame, the sparky is running first-fix cables, and you're overseeing the structural steels going in. Your phone's been ringing since half seven. A couple in St Albans want a rear extension — they've had planning approved and want to start before summer. A property investor in Hemel Hempstead needs three bathroom renovations across a buy-to-let portfolio. An architect in Bushey is looking for a reliable builder for a barn conversion project worth £80,000+. A previous customer in Rickmansworth calls to say rainwater is getting in around the patio doors you fitted last year. Every one of those calls matters. Without Rapid Receptionist, the extension lead calls another builder, the investor finds someone quicker, and the architect moves to the next name on his list. The customer complaint festers. With Rapid Receptionist, every call is answered, the architect lead is captured with full details, and you know about the patio door issue before it becomes a bad review."
  faqs={faqs}
/>
